The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 Four people have lost sight in one eye after cataract operations at RG Kar Medical College and Hospital on Monday. Gurupada Chanda, 52, Badal Dey, 64, Swarnamayee Sarkar, 78, and Latika Ghosh, 60, underwent the surgery on October 19. They were readmitted to the hospital on October 27. Tests have revealed that while Chanda had partially lost sight in one eye, the other three had suffered cornea damage. Medical superintendent K. Roy said a four-member committee has been formed to probe the incident. 

 The state government will introduce an area-based property tax regime in the city at the earliest, urban development and municipal affairs minister Asoke Bhattacharya said on Monday. We have to introduce it early, as it is a pre-condition for obtaining ADB loans and also funds under the Centres urban renewal mission. The system will later be implemented in Salt Lake, Asansol and Siliguri, the minister added. The Assembly select committee will examine the changes to the Calcutta Municipal Act on Tuesday. 

 Arijit Dolui, 22, was found hanging at his residence in Ramrajatala, Howrah, on Monday morning. He was taken to the district hospital, where he was pronounced dead. Police said Dolui had committed suicide after an altercation with his family.

 Roshan Singh, 17, drowned in the Hooghly while taking a bath on Sunday evening. He was a resident of Round Tank Lane, under Howrah police station. He was rescued by some onlookers, but died while being taken to hospital. 

 One person died and 20, including eight schoolchildren, were injured in separate road accidents in Howrah on Monday. An unidentified man in his 40s died after being knocked down by a vehicle in Jagachha. The body has been sent for post-mortem.

 welve persons were injured when the Matador they were travelling in overturned in Domjur. The injured were admitted to the district hospital. Eight children were injured when a school bus fell into a ditch in Sankrail. They were taken to a local hospital, from where they were released after first-aid. 

 Chottu Singh was arrested in Barrackpore on Monday for stealing from a businessmans house in the locality. The stolen goods, ornaments worth nearly Rs 50,000 and Rs 3 lakh in cash, was found in a bush near an abandoned house in Noapara.

 The city and its neighbourhood experienced intermittent power cuts on Monday evening as the shortfall in the CESC-served areas shot up to 140 MW. 

 Sports minister Subhas Chakraborty inaugurated the 55th All India Police Aquatic Meet and Cross Country Race 2006 at Subhas Sarovar on Monday. The event is being organised by the state and city police. Governor Gopal Krishna Gandhi will be the chief guest at the closing ceremony on November 10.

